        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;"> Global plastic crisis </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> Researchers warn of a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-9-aug-25-recap-h1-6-1-5-trillion-global-plastics-crisis?source=website" target="_blank">$1.5 trillion global plastics crisis</a> harming both human health and the planet. They assert that less than 10% of total plastics are recycled, while most end up in landfills, incinerators, or open fires, polluting the air and damaging ecosystems. Plastic production has increased more than 200-fold since 1950 and is projected to almost triple by 2060, exceeding 1Bn tonnes annually. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> The health risks from exposure to plastic fumes, chemicals, and microplastics include miscarriage, cancer, stroke, lung issues, and fertility issues. Micro and nanoplastics are found in human blood, brains, and placentas. While over 100 countries support a legally binding <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-9-aug-25-recap-h1-7-global-plastics-treaty?source=website" target="_blank">Global Plastics Treaty</a> to cap plastic production, powerful petrochemical nations and industry lobbyists are delaying progress. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;"> Lebanon to disarm Hezbollah </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> Lebanon’s Cabinet has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-9-aug-25-recap-h2-8-approved-a-us-backed-plan?source=website" target="_blank">approved a US-backed plan</a> to bring all weapons under state control by the end of 2025. This move would essentially disarm Hezbollah, the Iran-backed Shiite militant group and political party that operates independently of state authority. However, Hezbollah’s deputy leader, Naim Qassem, rejected the plan, stating they will not disarm while Israel continues attacks on Lebanon. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> Historically, Hezbollah was the only militia that did not disarm after the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-9-aug-25-recap-h2-9-lebanese-1975-1990-civil-war?source=website" target="_blank">Lebanese 1975–1990 civil war</a>, maintaining weapons for “resistance” against Israel. Currently, it is the world’s most heavily armed non-state actor. Israel continues to strike Hezbollah targets in Lebanon despite the ceasefire, and has made clear it will continue attacking until Hezbollah is fully disarmed. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;"> Was the Titan implosion preventable? </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> The US Coast Guard has concluded that the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-9-aug-25-recap-h3-10-2023-titan-submersible-implosion?source=website" target="_blank">2023 Titan submersible implosion</a>, which killed five people on a $250,000 deep-sea dive to the Titanic wreck, was entirely preventable. The report exposes how OceanGate bypassed safety norms, pressured employees, and manipulated regulatory gaps to operate an unsafe vessel. It revealed that OceanGate used intimidation and its good reputation to evade scrutiny.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> This tragedy sheds light on the growing industry of extreme tourism, where wealthy thrill-seekers pursue high-risk, one-of-a-kind experiences, often into unsafe or unstable environments. Some tourism ventures provide “survival trips” in places like the Amazon, where tourists learn primitive skills. As adventure tourism grows by up to 15% annually, the absence of adequate oversight and realistic risk assessments has led to preventable losses like the Titan tragedy.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
